[Pertussis has been on the increase throughout most of the world. This has been attributed in part to increased virulence and other genetic changes in the circulating clones of _Bordetella pertussis_, as well as waning or an ineffective immune response after vaccination. For a discussion of these problems, see moderator LL's comments in prior ProMED-mail posts on pertussis and moderator ML's comments in ProMED-mail post Pertussis - USA (04): (MT, CA) increased incidence 20140424.2426383.

Weld County, with a population that was 252 825 in 2010, is one of the 64 counties of the U.S. state of Colorado and is located in northeast Colorado, on the state's northern border with the state of Wyoming [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Weld_County,_Colorado]. A map of Colorado, showing the location of Weld County and the town of Windsor can be found at https://www.google.com/maps/place/Weld+County,+CO/@41.4173904,-106.3747581,6z/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x876c07da939b130b:0x79c8bbfa1c2ef9fa. - Mod.ML

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2833302,209.]
